SON LIBRARY for PYTHON.

For reading data from CED's Spike2 Son files.

Based on SON Library 2.0 for MATLAB, written by Malcolm Lidierth at
King's College London. See http://www.kcl.ac.uk/depsta/biomedical/
cfnr/lidierth.html

+ Using the library +
For details read the file __init__.py, or type the following in a Python
shell (after placing the sonpy directory in your Python search path):
>>> from sonpy import son
>>> help(son)


